# Organizational Unit (OU) Structure

## 📌 Overview
This Active Directory environment is structured using Organizational Units (OUs) to reflect a typical enterprise organizational hierarchy. Each OU represents a department and is used to apply role-based access control and Group Policy Objects (GPOs).

## 🧱 OU Design

The domain is organized into the following OUs:

- ADMINS
- Executives
- Finance
- HR
- IT
- Marketing
- Operations
- Sales

Each OU contains:
- User accounts
- Security groups
- Department-specific policies

## 🧠 Design Objectives

- Separate users by department
- Apply targeted security policies using GPOs
- Support least privilege access control
- Simplify administration and policy enforcement

## 🔐 Security Groups

Each OU includes security groups used for:
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Permission assignment to resources
- Managing administrative privileges

Examples:
- Finance_Users
- HR_Users
- IT_Admins
- Sales_Users

## ⚙️ Group Policy Application

Group Policy Objects (GPOs) are linked to each OU to enforce security configurations based on department requirements.

Examples:
- ADMINS: Enhanced logging and monitoring
- Executives: Restricted system access and enforced screen lock
- Finance: File auditing and removable media restrictions
- IT: Advanced logging with fewer restrictions

## 🔍 Benefits of OU Structure

- Centralized management of users and policies
- Scalable design for adding new departments
- Improved security through policy segmentation
- Easier troubleshooting and administration

